TY  - JOUR
T1  - Optimum Time Compression in Project Scheduling
AU  - Lamberson, L. R.
AU  - Hocking, R. R.
Y1  - 1970/06/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.10.B597
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.10.B597
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - B-597
EP  - B-606
VL  - 16
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - An algorithm based on convex programming is developed for optimum time compression in network scheduling systems. The development allows for the activity time-cost trade-off functions to be any differentiable convex function. Decomposition theory is then applied to reduce the amount of computation necessary. This along with a limited number of rules to structure any incoming vector makes the algorithm amenable to time compression in large project networks.
AB  - An algorithm based on convex programming is developed for optimum time compression in network scheduling systems. The development allows for the activity time-cost trade-off functions to be any differentiable convex function. Decomposition theory is then applied to reduce the amount of computation necessary. This along with a limited number of rules to structure any incoming vector makes the algorithm amenable to time compression in large project networks.
